{
  "text": "Although there have been notable improvements in exact hypervolume calculation in the last decade, it is still the case that for high k and/or |A| its calculation can be prohibitively expensive as a real-time cost. This has resulted in researchers using approximate approaches (including recent work on hybridised approaches [CITATION_1] ).",
  "citation_candidates": [
